      "span_text": "Integrins, including ␣ v ␤ 3 , play an important role in angiogenesis.  Also, FGF2 binds ␣ v ␤ 3 , and this interaction is required for endothelial cell response to the growth factor. 14 -16 The capacity of K5 derivatives to inhibit endothelial cell sprouting similar to the integrin antagonist c(RGDfV) prompted us to assess the possibility that K5 derivatives may affect FGF2/ ␣ v ␤ 3 interaction."
